{"badges":["TM5","TM6"],"usefulItems":"bowl, dariole mould (Ø 8 cm, 160 ml capacity each), freezer","id":"r127240","imageLink":"https:\/\/1.bp.blogspot.com\/-Ztf38yE7iFc\/XZWcnEZZCCI\/AAAAAAAAecE\/0NPB54UpnfgD4HaP2V6gsA-PN-rBML-GACLcBGAsYHQ\/s1600\/0_2bBftikbKgiSLIdM.png","title":"Strawberry and pear pudding","publishedAt":"2017-08-07T00:00:00Z","ingredients":[{"isHeader":true,"content":"Ingredients"},{"content":"20 g gelatine leaves (approx. 10 leaves)"},{"content":"75 g water"},{"content":"75 - 80 g lemon juice (approx. 2 lemons)"},{"content":"1000 g pears, peeled and cut into pieces"},{"content":"6 tbsp sugar"},{"content":"750 g strawberries, cut into slices"}],"nutrition":{"protein":"1 g","fat":"0.3 g","uom":"per 1 portion","carbohydrates":"11 g","calories":"212 kJ \/ 51 kcal"},"preparations":[{"isHeader":true,"content":"Preparation"},{"content":"Soak gelatine leaves in a bowl with cold water."},{"content":"Place water and lemon juice into mixingbowl and heat <b>3 min\/100°C\/speed 3<b>."},{"content":"Add pear pieces and cook <b>10 min\/80°C\/speed 2<b>. Remove mixing bowl and wait a few minutes for it to cool."},{"content":"Add soaked and well strained gelatine and sugar and blend <b>10 sec\/speed 10<b>."},{"content":"In 10 dariole moulds, place a layer of sliced strawberries and pour in some pear gelatine. Put ramekins in freezer until the mixture sets and hardens (so that the layers are well defined)."},{"content":"Divide ⅓ of the pear gelatine over the ramekins and let set again. Add another layer of strawberry slices and repeat the entire process ending with slices of strawberry and pear gelatine. Keep in refrigerator and remove from ramekins the following day before serving."}],"hintsAndTricks":["You can also use a cake mould (31 x 15 x 10 cm). If you use a metal mould, line it with cling film."],"basicInfo":["easy","30m","24h 30m","12 portions"]}